<Issue id="15927" key="FAB-3335" number="3335" project="10002" reporter="yacovm" assignee="yacovm" creator="yacovm" type="10004" summary="Gossip pull may send zero-length digests" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-04-22 10:08:44.0" updated="2018-07-20 14:12:20.0" resolutiondate="2017-04-22 20:02:20.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="38109"> <description><! CDATA The bug was introduced in a  recent commit | https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/c/8077/12/gossip/gossip/algo/pull.go@299  that added filtering capability.  Basically when the gossip puller gets a hello from a peer, it iterates over the items it has, and applies a filter on each of them. If the filter doesn't permit, it skips to the next iteration, but the returned slice then contains an "empty-string" digest in the response to the remote peer.  This bug blocks me from fixing https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/c/8081/ 's test, so I shall upload a fix now.   ></description> </Issue>
